description: I take all my lessons online via zoom meetings. My lessons focus on teaching a way of thinking aimed at solving problems. I do so by integrating basic mathematical principles with fundamental coding approaches before moving on to more advanced concepts. My lessons are highly suitable for students who want to start learning programming from scratch and also for those who need help with understanding specific difficult concepts.

I am a full-stack Software Engineer with a Master's degree from UNSW specialized in Data Science and E-Commerce. I have 2 years of experience in tutoring, more than 4 years of work experience as a software developer. I have expertise in Html/CSS/Javascript, Java, C#, Python, NodeJS, ReactJS, SQL, MongoDB databases, Rest API, Web Designing, and many industrial technologies. I have been tutoring students for the past 2 years and I served as a senior and tech lead at my work, guiding the team with programming and working standards. I will provide simple tasks to understand your current level and explain all the concepts with supporting examples and practice. We will have fun programming creative web applications and solving puzzles.

My teaching flavour depends on who I am teaching. I put together a unique course tailored for each student. This can include projects, step by step tutorials, and problem solving activities, all with a focus on a hands on learning. I have been teaching for many years and still work making games in the games industry as a day job as well as tutoring many regular students. I would love to help you make awesome stuff too, so feel free to message me and we can talk about what I can offer you.

My teaching method is very much based on achieving an outcome that resonates with students. Then tying that back to fundamentals so that we arenâ€™t just learning how to do things in specific environments, but so that you can take those skills and build on them to solve your own problems. I like story telling and explaining concepts in plain English before diving into the technicalities. I consider it a way of building bridges between where a student is and their intended destination.

My teaching methodology is flexible which means I teach according to their learning pace. According to their learning capacity, I organise the lessons to serve the motive of the lectures. I usually explain problems by giving them the examples which is the practical way to learn something new.IT graduate from Victoria University and completed my degree with distinction. I have 3 years teaching experience. I am expert in web technologies HTML, CSS, SASS, JavaScript , functional javascript, jQuery,Bootstrap and React. I have created some websites using these Technologies and earned certifications in these technologies.

I believe in learning by doing. My teaching focuses on creating the fundamental intuition first and building up gradually. This not only cements the why of what I teach, but also gives the student a clear goal of what is important. For this purpose, my classes include numerous interesting and relevant examples. I am a physics graduate in WA, with a masters and doing a PhD in Astrophysics. My experience involves programming using different tools and languages, especially python, to unravel information from data

My teaching method is focused on the students themselves. Every person holds different backgrounds, like their own previous skills and tastes. Aligning the subject taught with these former interests is key to have an enjoyable learning experience. Beyond that, building up on top of basics skills and exercising creativeness alongside with problem tackling strategies has been giving the best outcomes I ever came across. I am a Business Analyst and Software Engineer and I have been giving lessons and teaching ever since I was a kid. I've taught computer science subjects as tutor and researcher during my university time.
